POSIX
-----

Specification-focused coverage transcribed from the [POSIX awk utility requirements](https://pubs.opengroup.org/onlinepubs/9699919799/utilities/awk.html).

<div class="row compat-row">
  <div class="col-sm-9">
    <div class="progress">
      <div class="progress-bar progress-bar-${posixType}" role="progressbar" aria-valuenow="${posixPercent}" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="100" style="width: ${posixPercent}%;">
        <span>${posixPassed} / ${posixTests}</span>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="compat-legend">
      <span class="compat-legend-item"><span class="compat-cell compat-cell-pass"></span> Passed</span>
      <span class="compat-legend-item"><span class="compat-cell compat-cell-failure"></span> Failed</span>
      <span class="compat-legend-item"><span class="compat-cell compat-cell-error"></span> Error</span>
      <span class="compat-legend-item"><span class="compat-cell compat-cell-skipped"></span> Skipped</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="col-sm-3">
    <div class="compat-suite-score">${posixPercent}%</div>
  </div>
</div>
<div class="compat-map" aria-label="POSIX compatibility map">
#foreach($testcase in $posixSummary.children())
#if($testcase.node().nodeName == "testcase")
#set($cellClass = "compat-cell-pass")
#if($testcase.attr('status') == "error")
#set($cellClass = "compat-cell-error")
#elseif($testcase.attr('status') == "failure")
#set($cellClass = "compat-cell-failure")
#elseif($testcase.attr('status') == "skipped")
#set($cellClass = "compat-cell-skipped")
#end
  <span class="compat-cell ${cellClass}" title="${testcase.attr('classname')}.${testcase.attr('name')}"></span>
#end
#end
</div>

<p class="compat-suite-footer"><a href="failsafe.html#io-jawk-posix">Open the Failsafe report</a> for per-test details, stack traces, and grouped results.</p>

